[+] Environment Setup
    [+] Install Python and IDE (e.g., Spyder via Anaconda or use online IDE)
    [+] Install required libraries (NumPy, Matplotlib, SciPy, scikit-learn, PyTorch, Torchvision)
[+] Task 1: Basel Climate Dataset
    [+] Load dataset and initial data inspection
        [+] Check for missing data
        [+] Verify data types and shapes
    [ ] Data Pre-processing
        [+] Standardize features
        [ ] Normalize features
        [ ] Outlier detection and treatment
        [ ] Feature selection/extraction (e.g., PCA)
    [ ] Clustering Analysis
        [ ] K-Means clustering
        [ ] Hierarchical clustering
        [ ] Independent research clustering method (e.g., DBSCAN, Spectral Clustering, K-Medoids)
        [ ] Cluster evaluation using quantitative metrics (Purity, Davies-Bouldin)
        [ ] Visualize clusters and centroids
    [ ] Documentation and critical analysis for Task 1
[ ] Task 2: Image Processing with DNNs
    [ ] Dataset & DNN Model Selection
        [ ] Choose and obtain two datasets (e.g., OxfordPetsIIIT, Food101, etc.)
        [ ] Select DNN model(s) for feature extraction (e.g., DinoV2, VGG16, ResNet)
    [ ] Image Preprocessing & Feature Extraction
        [ ] Resize and normalize images
        [ ] Extract feature vectors using chosen DNN(s)
        [ ] Dimensionality reduction (e.g., PCA, t-SNE, UMAP)
        [ ] Visualize feature vectors in 2D
    [ ] Clustering in Latent Space
        [ ] Perform clustering on latent feature vectors
        [ ] Evaluate cluster quality (Purity, Davies-Bouldin, etc.)
    [ ] Classification
        [ ] Apply linear fine-tuning (LFT) and/or alternative classifiers (kNN, SVM, Decision Tree)
        [ ] Compute performance metrics (Accuracy, Confusion Matrix, Precision, Recall, F1, computational complexity)
    [ ] Documentation and critical analysis for Task 2
[ ] Report Writing and Submission
    [ ] Draft main report (≤6 pages, double-column)
    [ ] Prepare Appendix (code, extended results, ≤4 pages)
    [ ] Add abstract, introduction, conclusion, acknowledgments, references
    [ ] Add appropriate code and analysis samples
    [ ] Final review for completeness and clarity
    [ ] Submit code and report